antry Regiment|68th Indiana]]: Ltc Harvey J. Espy ('''w'''), Cpt Richard L. Leeson\n*[[8th Regiment Kansas Volunteer Infantry|8th Kansas]]: Col [[John Martin (Governor of Kansas)|John A. Martin]]\n*[[15th Ohio Infantry|15th Ohio]]: Ltc Frank Askew\n*[[49th Ohio Infantry|49th Ohio]]: Maj Samuel F. Gray\n*[[15th Wisconsin Volunteer Regiment|15th Wisconsin]]: Cpt John A. Gordon\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William B. Hazen]]\n|\n*[[6th Indiana Infantry Regiment|6th Indiana]]: Maj Calvin D. Campbell\n*[[5th Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|5th Kentucky]]: Col William W. Berry ('''w'''),<ref>Commanded part of time 6th Indiana and 5th Kentucky (''see: Berry's report'')</ref> Ltc John L. Treanor\n*[[6th Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|6th Kentucky]]: Maj Richard T. Whitaker\n*[[23rd Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|23rd Kentucky]]: Ltc James C. Foy<ref>Succeeded Lieutenant Colonel Langdon in command of the 23rd Kentucky and 1st Ohio (''see: Stafford's report'')</ref>\n*[[1st Ohio Infantry|1st Ohio]]: Ltc Bassett Langdon<ref>Commanded part of time 23rd Kentucky and 1st Ohio (''see: Foy's and Stafford's report'')</ref> ('''w'''), Maj Joab A. Stafford<ref>Wounded but remained on the field</ref> ('''w''')\n*[[6th Ohio Infantry|6th Ohio]]: Ltc Alexander C. Christopher\n*[[41st Ohio Infantry|41st Ohio]]: Col [[Aquila Wiley]]<ref>Commanded part of time 41st Ohio and 93rd Ohio (''see: Kimberly's and Smith's report'')</ref> ('''w'''), Ltc Robert L. Kimberly<ref>Succeeded Colonel Wiley in command of the 41st Ohio and 93rd Ohio (''see: Kimberly's and Smith's report'')</ref>\n*[[93rd Ohio Infantry|93rd Ohio]]: Maj William Birch ('''mw'''), Cpt Daniel Bowman ('''w'''), Cpt Samuel B. Smith\n*[[124th Ohio Infantry|124th Ohio]]: Ltc James Pickands\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Samuel Beatty (general)|Samuel Beatty]]\n|\n*[[79th Regiment Indiana Infantry|79th Indiana]]: Col [[Frederick Knefler]]\n*[[86th Regiment Indiana Infantry|86th Indiana]]: Col 