io Infantry|61st Ohio]]: Col Stephen J. McGroarty\n*[[82nd Ohio Infantry|82nd Ohio]]: Ltc David Thomson\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Wladimir Krzyzanowski]]\n|\n*[[58th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|58th New York]]: Cpt Michael Esembaux\n*[[119th New York Volunteer Infantry|119th New York]]: Col John T. Lockman\n*[[141st New York Volunteer Infantry|141st New York]]: Col William K. Logie\n*[[26th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|26th Wisconsin]]: Cpt [[Frederick Charles Winkler|Frederick C. Winkler]]\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Frederick Hecker]]\n|\n*[[80th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|80th Illinois]]: Cpt James Neville\n*[[82nd Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|82nd Illinois]]: Ltc [[Edward S. Salomon]]\n*[[68th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|68th New York]]: Ltc Albert von Steinhausen\n*[[75th Pennsylvania Infantry|75th Pennsylvania]]: Maj August Ledig\n|-\n|\n| Artillery\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMaj [[Thomas W. Osborn]]\n|\n*1st New York Light, Battery I: Cpt Michael Wiedrich\n*New York Light, 13th Battery: Cpt William Wheeler\n*[[Battery I, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery I]]:<ref name=attachedFourth/> Cpt [[Hubert Dilger]]\n*[[Battery K, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery K]]: Lt Nicholas Sahm\n*[[4th U.S. Light Artillery, Battery G|4th United States, Battery G]]:<ref name=attachedFourth/> Lt Christopher F. Merkle\n|}\n\n=====[[XII Corps (Union Army)|XII Corps]]=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Division\n! width=25% | Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nSecond Division<ref>The First Division engaged in guarding the Nashville and Chattanooga Railroad from Wartrace Bridge, to Bridgeport, Alabama, etc. Major General [[Henry W. Slocum]], the corps commander, had his headquarters at Tullahoma, Tennessee.</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John W. Geary]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Charles Candy]]<ref>Disabled November 24, 1863</ref>\n<b