th Kentucky]] detached at Brown's Ferry, Tennessee</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Edward H. Phelps ('''k''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol William H. Hays\n|\n*[[10th Regiment Indiana Infantry|10th Indiana]]: Ltc Marsh B. Taylor\n*[[74th Regiment Indiana Infantry|74th Indiana]]: Ltc Myron Baker\n*[[4th Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|4th Kentucky]]: Maj Robert M. Kelly\n*[[10th Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|10th Kentucky]]: Col [[William Hercules Hays|William H. Hays]], Ltc Gabriel C. Wharton\n*[[14th Ohio Infantry|14th Ohio]]: Ltc Henry D. Kingsbury\n*[[38th Ohio Infantry|38th Ohio]]: Maj Charles Greenwood\n|-\n| Artllery\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt George R. Swallow\n|\n*[[7th Independent Battery Indiana Light Artillery|Indiana Light, 7th Battery]]: Lt Otho H. Morgan\n*[[9th Independent Battery Indiana Light Artillery|Indiana Light, 9th Battery]]: Lt Robert G. Lackey\n*[[4th U.S. Light Artillery, Battery I|4th United States, Battery I]]: Lt Frank G. Smith\n|}\n\n====Artillery Reserve====\nBG [[John M. Brannan]]<ref>Chief of Artillery, Army of the Cumberland</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Division\n! width=25% | Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nFirst Division\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol James Barnett\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMaj Charles S. Cotter\n|\n*[[Battery B, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery B]]: Lt Norman A. Baldwin\n*[[Battery C, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery C]]: Cpt Marco B. Gary\n*[[Battery E, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery E]]: Lt Albert G. Ransom\n*[[Battery F, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery F]]: Lt Giles J. Cokerill\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n|\n*[[Battery G, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery G]]: Cpt Alexander Marshall\n*[[Battery M, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery M]]: Cpt Frederick Schultz\n*[[18th Ohio Battery]]: Lt Joseph McCafferty\n*[[20th Ohio Battery]]:<ref>Temporarily attached to Third Division, Fourth Army Corps</ref> Cpt Edward Grosskopff\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nSecond Division\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt Josiah W. Church\n|\n*[[Battery \"D\" 1st Regiment Michigan Light Artillery|1st Michigan Light, Battery D]]: Cpt Josiah W. Church\n*[[1st Battalion Tennessee Light Artillery, Battery \"A\"|1st Tennessee Light, Battery A]]: Lt Albert F. Beach\n*[[3rd Independent Battery Wisconsin Light Artillery|Wisconsin Light, 3rd Battery]]: Lt Hiram F. Hubbard\n*[[8th Independent Battery Wisconsin Light Artillery|Wisconsin Light, 8th Battery]]: Lt Obadiah German\n*[[10th Independent Battery Wisconsin Light Artillery|Wisconsin Light, 10th Battery]]: Cpt Yates V. Beebe\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[Arnold Sutermeister]]\n|\n*[[4th Independent Battery Indiana Light Artillery|Indiana Light, 4th Battery]]: Lt Henry J. Willits\n*[[8th Independent Battery Indiana Light Artillery|Indiana Light, 8th Battery]]: Lt George Estep\n*[[11th Independent Battery Indiana Light Artillery|Indiana Light, 11th Battery]]: Cpt Arnold Sutermeister\n*[[21st Independent Battery Indiana Light Artillery|Indiana Light, 21st Battery]]: Lt William E. Chess\n*[[1st Wisconsin Heavy Artillery Regiment|1st Wisconsin Heavy, Company C]]: Cpt John R. Davies\n|}\n\n====[[Cavalry Corps (Union Army)#Western Cavalry Corps|Cavalry Corps]]====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Division\n! width=25% | Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=1 |\nSecond Division<ref>Corps headquarters and the First and Second Brigades and 18th Indiana Battery, of the First Division, at and about Alexandria, Tennessee; the Third Brigade at Caperton's Ferry, Tennessee River. The First and Third Brigades, and the Chicago Board, of Trade Battery, of the Second Division, at Maysville, Alabama.</ref>\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Eli Long]]\n|\n*[[98th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|98th Illinois Mounted Infantry]]: Ltc Edward Kitchell\n*[[17th Indiana Infantry Regiment|17th Indiana Mounted Infantry]]: Ltc Henry Jordan\n*[[2nd Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Cavalry|2nd Kentucky]]: Col Thomas P. Nichols\n*[[4th Michigan Cavalry|4th Michigan]]: Maj Horace Gray\n*[[1st Ohio Cavalry|1st Ohio]]: Maj Thomas J. Patten\n*[[3rd Ohio Cavalry|3rd Ohio]]: Ltc Charles B. Seidel\n*[[4th Ohio Cavalry|4th Ohio]]: Maj George W. Dobb\n*[[10th Ohio Cavalry|10th Ohio]]: Col Charles C. Smith\n|}\n\n====Engineers and garrison====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Division\n! width=25% | Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nEngineer troops\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William Farrar Smith|William F. Smith]]\n| Engineer Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Timothy Robbins Stanley|Timothy R. Stanley]]<ref>''John H. Eicher and David J. Eicher, Civil War High Commands, page 505''</ref>\n| \n*[[1st Regiment Michigan Volunteer Engineers and Mechanics|1st Michigan Engineers]] (detachment): Cpt Perrin V. Fox\n*[[18th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|18th Michigan]]: Maj Willard G. Eaton\n*[[21st Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|21st Michigan]]: Cpt Loomis K. Bishop\n*[[22nd Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|22nd Michigan]]: Maj Henry S. Dean\n*[[18th Ohio Infantry|18th Ohio]]: Col Timothy R. Stanley\n|-\n| [[Pioneer Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[George P. Buell]]\n| \n*1st Battalion: Cpt Charles J. Stewart\n*2nd Battalion: Cpt Correll Smith\n*3rd Battalion: Cpt William Clark\n|-\n| rowspan=1 |\nChattanooga garrison\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[James B. Steedman]]<ref>''John H. Eicher and [[David J. Eicher]], Civil War High Commands, page 507''</ref>\n| Post of Chattanooga\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol John G. Parkhurst\n| \n*[[44th Indiana Volunteer Infantry|44th Indiana]]: Ltc Simeon C. Aldrich\n*[[15th Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|15th Kentucky]]: Maj William G. Halpin\n*[[9th Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment|9th Michigan]]: Ltc William Wilkerson\n|}\n\n====Hooker's Command====\nMG [[Joseph Hooker]]<ref>Major General Joseph Hooker, commanding Eleventh and Twelfth Army Corps had under his immediate command the First Division, Fourth Corps, the Second Division, Twelfth Corps, portions of the Fourteenth Corps, and the First Division, Fifteenth Corps.</ref>\n\n*Chief of Staff: MG [[Daniel Butterfield|Daniel A. Butterfield]]\nEscort:\n*[[15th Regiment Illinois Volunteer Cavalry|15th Illinois Cavalry]], Company K: Cpt Samuel B. Sherer\n\n=====[[XI Corps (Union Army)|XI Corps]]=====\nMG [[Oliver O. Howard]]\n<br>\nGeneral Headquarters:\n*8th New York, Independent Company: Cpt Anton Bruhn\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Division\n! width=25% | Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nSecond Division\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Adolph von Steinwehr]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Adolphus Buschbeck]]\n|\n*[[33rd New Jersey Volunteer Infantry|33rd New Jersey]]: Col George W. Mindil\n*[[134th New York Volunteer Infantry|134th New York]]: Col Allan H. Jackson\n*[[154th New York Volunteer Infantry|154th New York]]: Col [[Patrick Henry Jones|Patrick H. Jones]]\n*[[27th Pennsylvania Infantry|27th Pennsylvania]]: Maj Peter A. McAloon ('''mw'''), Cpt August Riedt\n*[[73rd Pennsylvania Infantry|73rd Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Joseph B. Taft ('''k'''), Cpt Daniel F. Kelley ('''c'''), Lt Samuel D. Miller\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Orland Smith]]\n|\n*[[33rd Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|33rd Massachusetts]]: Ltc Godfrey Rider, Jr.\n*[[136th New York Volunteer Infantry|136th New York]]: Col [[James Wood (New York state senator)|James Wood]]\n*[[55th Ohio Infantry|55th Ohio]]: Col Charles B. Gambee\n*[[73rd Ohio Infantry|73rd Ohio]]: Maj Samuel H. Hurst\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nThird Division\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMG [[Carl Schurz]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Hector Tyndale]]\n|\n*[[101st Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|101st Illinois]]: Col Charles H. Fox\n*[[45th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|45th New York]]: Maj Charles Koch\n*[[143rd New