ps and the Second Division, Fourteenth Corps, of the Army of the Cumberland; the Second and Fourth Divisions, Fifteenth Corps.</ref>\n\n====[[XV Corps (Union Army)|XV Corps]]====\nMG [[Francis P. Blair, Jr.|Francis P. Blair]]<ref>The Third Division, Brigadier General James M. Tuttle commanding, at Memphis, La Grange, and Pocahontas, Tennessee.</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Division\n! width=25% | Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nFirst Division\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Peter J. Osterhaus]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Charles R. Woods]]\n|\n*[[13th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|13th Illinois]]: Ltc Frederick W. Partridge ('''w'''), Maj Douglas R. Bushnell ('''k'''), Cpt George P. Brown\n*[[3rd Missouri Volunteer Infantry|3rd Missouri]]: Ltc Theodore Meumann\n*[[12th Missouri Volunteer Infantry|12th Missouri]]: Col Hugo Wangelin ('''w'''), Ltc Jacob Kaercher\n*[[17th Missouri Volunteer Infantry|17th Missouri]]: Col John F. Cramer\n*[[27th Missouri Volunteer Infantry|27th Missouri]]: Col [[Thomas Curley (Wisconsin)|Thomas Curley]]\n*[[29th Missouri Volunteer Infantry|29th Missouri]]: Col James Peckham ('''w'''), Maj Philip H. Murphy\n*[[31st Missouri Volunteer Infantry|31st Missouri]]: Ltc Samuel P. Simpson\n*[[32nd Missouri Volunteer Infantry|32nd Missouri]]: Ltc Henry C. Warmoth\n*[[76th Ohio Infantry|76th Ohio]]: Maj Willard Warner\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[James Alexander Williamson|James A. Williamson]]\n|\n*[[4th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|4th Iowa]]: Ltc George Burton\n*[[9th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|9th Iowa]]: Col David Carskaddon\n*[[25th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|25th Iowa]]: Col George A. Stone\n*[[26th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|26th Iowa]]: Col Milo Smith\n*[[30th Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|30th Iowa]]: Ltc Aurelius Roberts\n*[[31st Iowa Volunteer Infantry Regiment|31st Iowa]]: Ltc Jeremiah W. Jenkins\n|-\n| Artillery\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt H